/// A switch on this result with two destinations can be converted to a single
/// icmp if the cases cover two of the three possible values.
/// For example:
///   switch (ucmp(a, b)) { case -1: case 0: goto dst; }
/// is equivalent to:
///   if (a <= b) goto dst; else goto default;
/// which can be further optimized to:
///   if (a > b) goto default; else goto dst;
